&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Accountant is part of the Finance Department and focuses on high-volume transactional processes, including (but not limited to) accounts receivable, collections, accounts payable, and general ledger activities. The team consists of Accounting Managers, Senior Accountants, and Accountants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Accounting Manager (or Senior Accountant), this role is an integral part of the global accounting team. The Accountant is responsible for month-end close activities, financial analysis, reconciliations, and support during financial audits. The position offers exposure to multiple areas of Cision through reporting and analysis of actual financial results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes, but is not limited to, the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly journal entries related to bank activities, prepaid expenses, property, plant and equipment, accrued expenses, payroll accounting, and intercompany accounting, in line with close timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and maintain monthly balance sheet reconciliations, addressing questions from reviewers and management in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders, including international accounting teams, FP&amp;amp;A, Legal, and external consultants, particularly in relation to flux analysis and ad-hoc support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare audit schedules and proactively respond to auditor queries, resolving audit issues as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with footnote tie-outs for quarterly and year-end financial statements prepared under US GAAP and IFRS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support statutory financial reporting and statutory audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
